        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 8:10PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 810 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Leeds, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whitney Junction, Ragland, Mountain Brook, Wattsville, Shops of Grand
River, Bald Rock, I 59 Rest Areas At Oneonta, Liberty Park, Margaret,
Barber Motorsports Park, Vestavia Hills, Camp Winnataska, Harrisburg,
Branchville, Greystone, Inverness, Grants Mill Road Bridge, St. Clair
Springs, Cahaba Heights, and Leeds.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
